This paper is primarily focused on learning visual representations from egocentric video, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of proprioceptive motor signals to regularize the learning process, which is related to robotics (cs.RO). The use of unsupervised learning methods to learn visual representations also falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the application of the learned features to improve scene recognition, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE).
